ABSTRACT The present study was designed to investi- gate the effects of conjugated linoleic acid (CLA) on yolk usage and circulating very low density lipoproteins (VLDL) during incubation (Day 15) and through 6 d post- hatch. Eggs enriched with CLA were obtained from hens subjected to the following treatments. Group A hens served as the control group, Group B hens received 1 g CLA every other day, Group C hens received 1 g CLA every 4th d, and Group D hens were sham-supplemented with 1 g safflower oil every other day. Enrichment with CLA did not effect fertility, hatch of fertile, BW, or yolk- free BW of embryos or chicks.
